        <div id="en">
            <h3>Ingredients:</h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Potatoes</li>
                <li>Vegetable oil(adequate amount to submerge fries)</li>
                <li>Salt (Adequate)</li>
                <li>Optional seasonings (like red chilli powder,garlic powder, black pepper)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Process:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Wash and peel the potatoes.</li>
                <li>Cut the potatoes into uniform, thin strips.</li>
                <li>Soak them in cold water for at least 30 minutes.</li>
                <li>After soaking, drain the fries and pat them dry with a kitchen towel.</li>
                <li>Heat vegetable oil in a deep pot or a deep fryer,until you see many small bubbles forming around it.</li>
                <li>Carefully add a small batch of the dried potato strips to the hot oil. Do not to overcrowd the pot.</li>
                <li>Fry the potatoes until they turn light golden. Remove with a slotted spoon and place them on a plate lined with paper towels to drain excess oil.</li>
                <li>Repeat this process with the remaining batches of potato strips.</li>
                <li><b>(optional) </b>For extra crispy French fries, you can do a double fry. After the first fry, allow the fries to cool for a few minutes and again fry them,and again fry them until they become golden brown.</li>
                <li>While the fries are hot, season them with salt and any other seasonings as above mentioned in ingredients. Toss the fries to evenly coat them with the seasonings.</li>
                <li>Serve the homemade French fries immediately while they're still hot and crispy. You can enjoy them with ketchup, mayonnaise, or your favorite dipping sauces.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enjoy your homemade french fries :)</p>
